race.comment: VORTISTAR (7) resumed from a spell last start beaten a half-length over 1200m at Launceston. He'd switched from a Victorian stable and has more to give over the longer sprint. Rates to win with average luck in the run. NORTHERN CHILD (4) draws even wider but presents off an improved effort at Launceston. Comes back 200m on a three-week return and he will be fitter again. DA SILVER FLASH (11) was on pace here over 1400 and gave it away late. He will have taken improvement and will carry just 52kg with the claim. She will be tougher to stop today. SAVAGE RIVER (5) needs to find more but has a handy 2kg claim and plenty of scope for improvement.
